23/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul met with Iraqi Kurdistan Patriotic Union chairman Celal Talabani on Tuesday (22 June), reportedly discussing recent developments in Iraq and a possible joint operation against Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) militants holed up in northern Iraq.
During his visit to Ankara, Talabani condemned recent PKK terror attacks on the Turkish Army.
In other news, Turkey learned Tuesday that it has been removed from the Council of Europe's human rights watch list.
In Ankara, the foreign ministry described the development as overcoming another hurdle to starting EU membership talks.
(Cihan News, Bloomberg - 22/06/04)
